[00:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Hey, my name is Ethan. I am the founding designer here at Flora and I\'m really excited to share styles with you. Something we\'ve been working really hard on bringing uh into the Flora editor and it is now ready to share with you all. So styles basically let you control your generations and your outputs inside of'

[00:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Flora with a lot more precision and a lot more reliability and a lot more creative control. Um, so these are things like aesthetics, tone, color, mood, um, even content from characters to objects inside of your generations.'

[00:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Um, and again creating those with a lot more consistency and reliability without having to worry too much about prompting or prompt engineering. Um, so I\'ll get started. So you\'ll see in I\'m in a blank'

[00:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'floor editor. Normally, I go ahead and double click to create a new block, but this time I\'m going to bring you over to the left side toolbar. And you\'ll see there\'s actually a new icon here. And'

[00:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'this is our styles menu. So, if we hover over, you\'ll see all of these brand new styles that we\'ve actually just trained specifically. These are really, really high quality, um, nicely trained styles for you to use as starting points. And'

[01:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'we just made all of these specific for this launch. Um, so these are styles that we thought would be really useful across all kinds of creative disciplines. So from fashion to film making to um product photography, game'

[01:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'design, etc. So um this is like a pretty wide range for inspiration and also as a starting point. Of course you can train your own style on your own content which I\'ll show you in a moment. Um but again'

[01:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'this is a really great starting point. Uh, so if you hover over this menu, you\'ll see this kind of quick menu, but if you click, you\'ll get the full menu here. So, um, if you go to all, again, these are the styles that we\'ve'

[01:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'pre-inccluded, but also you\'ll see this my styles tab, and this is where your custom styles will go. Um, in this case, I\'ve trained two that I can show in a moment. Um, but I\'ll also show you how'

[02:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to train your own style. So, let\'s get started with let\'s see motion blur. I really like motion'

[02:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'blur. So, we can either click or we can drag this out into the canvas and it will pop it into a brand new image block. And you\'ll see up here in the block toolbar, there\'s now a style dropdown that\'s been redesigned and it'

[02:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'will show you all of those same styles that we saw in this side panel, but they\'re accessible via the block as well. Um, if we make a brand new image block, you\'ll see also there\'s no style'

[02:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'applied by default, but we have all of those same uh styles that we can apply and all of your custom styles of course will be included in here as well. Um, so in this case again we have our motion'

[02:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
